On Fedora 16 run the setup.sh shell script with an internet connection and as root
. setup.sh

otherwise follow the following directions

Step 1: install mysql

fedora 16
$yum install mysql mysql-server
fedora 12-15
$yum --enablerepo=remi install mysql mysql-server

Step 2: start mysql

$/bin/systemctl start mysqld.service #starts sql server
$/bin/systemctl enable mysqld.service #sets mysql to restart on boot

Step 3: setup database in mysql

$mysql -u root < dbSetup.sql

step 4: install ruby and gems

step5: run the program
$ruby em.rb <failed attempts> <ban length in minutes> <logfile>

